content.detailedDescription: I was at the bottom of south mountain in phoenix arizona. watching from ground level my girlfriend noticed a blue orb moving across the horizon. as she pointed it out to me, the orb stopped and disappeared. then re-appeared in the same spot. and continued doing that as it moved across the sky. a few days later i was in the same location with my father working on my car and he spotted another orb, but this one was red he called me over to see it. as we watched it hovering for about 30 seconds, it made a violent turn to the east slightly descending. at that exact moment it either turned into a green orb or it split into 2 orbs red & green. hard to tell, happened very quick. then a few moments later, a loud "boom" like a cannon.. made us jump and continued throughout the night every 15 minutes or so. no media coverage of these loud "booms" and they shook the ground we stood on. however not as bad as a sonic boom. a little more subtle.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering,Other
content.summary: Blue orb moving across horizon. then stopped as i spotted it. 2 more orbs that week red turned violently green changed direction followed by loud booms

content.detailedDescription: This is my second sighting in a few months.  this time there were 2 other witnesses.  the craft flew right over us and was very quiet. i noticed a triangle shape and my girlfriend said it was a hexagon. bright red and green lights that blinked sometimes, but not a steady pattern. it was flying pretty low, about 400-500 ft above and was very quiet.  when it passed us we ran upstairs to our attic apartment and watched it travel east down the saco river, when it stated moving up and down really fast. in the distance we thought we seen it beam a light down as well.  it proceeded to fly north towards old orchard beach.  this is the same craft i witnessed a few months ago, this time i got a much better view of it. it was definitely not a plane, helo, or drone.
content.summary: Large, quiet craft with red and green lights flying over biddeford/saco

content.detailedDescription: I was taking many pictures of a beautiful sunset with my samsung s5 phone. the view is due west over the strait of juan de fuca from fort ebey state park on whidbey island in puget sound. my first edit after taking them was to get rid of all that weren't good compositions. that took awhile as there were way over 100 photos. much later i started checking the sharpness of the images. that's when i noticed 3 of them that had this strange shape in them. the shape came up from the northwest horizon & eventually ended up almost due west at 25 or 30 degrees above the horizon. it doesn't look like any aircraft i know of, though there is a naval airbase nearby & lots of float planes in the area shuttling people to/from the nearby san juan islands resort area. i'm interested in knowing what the object is.
content.summary: Round with 4 objects on the side that seem to go from dark to light

content.detailedDescription: I was in my backyard smoking a cigarette looking up at the sky like i usually do. i saw what i thought was a satellite. a burst of light came from the rear of it and made it move faster for a brief moment. this sequence happened about five times during which time the object slightly curved from northwest to southeast. i wasn’t particularly surprised because i have seen other objects before and look for them frequently, however, it has been a couple years since i have seen anything worth reporting to mufon. lost sight of it due to foliage on the trees. this was a first for me seeing something that moved like this object. who knows.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving down a road when i saw two bright lights in the field to my right. they didn't appear to be moving like a plane and were brighter/larger than lights coming from a plane at night. i followed them for a half mile until i got to the curve in the road that ends near the ocean. i turned my car around and the object was hovering in front of my car staying somewhat still. it had two bight yellow lights and a small red blinking light in the middle. at first it was hard to tell if it was a large aircraft far away or a drone close up. i think it may have been a drone. i turned my car around and the object was flying to my right above the treeline alongside my car. as i turned down a driveway the object continued and flew northwest over the woods. i didn't hear any loud noises coming from the object (i was in my running car though). i've heard that nice drones are quite loud and it is also illegal to fly drones out of eyesight in maine. if it was someone's drone they were not within eyesight of it as it flew over a field, woods and houses.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Two bright yellow lights with one red blinking light, may have been a drone

content.detailedDescription:
In the kitchen at 11:50pm making sleep tea.  looked out the window in the back door and saw a deer like animal about 10 feet from the door. it's body was barrel shaped, post set on legs, body to long for normal deer, to tall and head moved up and down, left and right. no movement to the ears. have watch a doe with her fawn for past 6 wks eating plants in my flower garden. this night the doe and fawn went flying in full panic mode between the swing set and this other deer.  this animal just watched it fly by and looked back at me. normal deer would followed these two and not have just stood there. i have jumped deer walking and watched them flee. this doe and fawn were just a flash.

would like you to know that i have selected sires for a dairy herd for over 20 years and know how to judge an animals appearance.   we have had up to eight deer outside the house during the winter months. this one was not normal in any regard. 

the next thing i see are two black eyes in front of my face, turned to leave the door and felt cold air on my back. did not fully make the turn, was still bring by left foot forward when the eyes were in front of me again. i could not move and did not want it in my house.  could feel heat on top of my head that grew more intense along with the feeling of complete and total peace. tranquility, but did not want it there, but it felt so good i was no longer able to stop it from happening. next thing i know i'm standing about 5ft from the door with my house coat tied all bunched up at my waist feeling disoriented and like something is wrong, not right.  when i check the time it was 3:38am the next morning.

in the morning woke up with a small round scab on top my head with dry, totally dehydrated blood to the nape of my neck and a small lump on my head. by night there were small welts on my lower legs.  these went away with in 12 hrs and new ones would come, this went on for two to two a half week and itched like crazy.  used all kind of lotions, nothing total took the itching away.
content.summary: Got up at 11:50pm when checked the clock 3:38am  missing time.  this was the 4th time in 7 months.  morning round scabe on head with dried blood to nape of neck. 4 different events of missing time.

content.detailedDescription:
I was outside looking for meteors during the taurid meteor time frame, 11/12/2017 at about 00:05. i saw a set dim lights in a triangle formation just above the horizon to the nw. it passed directly overhead. i lost sight of it as it entered the city light glow just above the horizon to the sw. 

the lights were equidistant apart, essentially in the configuration of a equilateral triangle. the object caught my attention as i initially saw it, thinking it was an owl. i immediately realized it was not an owl because of the 3 equidistant lights. 

i thought for a moment that maybe 3 meteors were together. however, the lights stayed equidistant apart, traveled together in a straight path and had no trail behind them.  the lights also stayed consistent in illumination, neither flaring or dimming as they moved. the stars above it were blocked as it passed over head indicating the area between the lights was a solid object. 

the object moved across the sky in less than 1.5 seconds.  it was completely silent. 

i often see aircraft overhead, small planes, airliners, f-16s, a-10s, etc.  i have seen never anything travel across the sky that fast.

i have never seen anything like this is the past. i am a non-drinker, was sober and awake and have over 34 years of law enforcement experience.  

the sighting was too quick for photos or videos.
content.summary: Saw 3 dim white lights in triangle shape fly across clear sky from horizon to horizon in about 1.5 seconds.

content.detailedDescription: I was on the carnival magic cruise ship on the morning of 11/5 we were heading toward amber cove dr, but were still out to sea heading southeast. i woke eaarly and was sitting on the balcony of our room. it was very clear. i first saw 2 small shooting starts come from the south and burned out just passed orion. shortly after that a brighter shooting start came from overhead flying easterly in same direction of the others, but then it stopped for 1 to 2 seconds and then it shot off northerly. i saw it for several more seconds until it was gone from view. it was too high to be a helicopter, it was solid white and very high. it was not a satellite as it was moving far to fast.

content.detailedDescription:
I was a corrections officer at evans correctional facility located in bennettsville,sc. i was on duty that night and assigned to be outside monitoring the perimeter of the prison. at the time of the event i was driving the security truck 10 miles an hour around the outermost fence of the entire prison. the prison fence is in the shape of a rectangle but with rounded corners. as i came around one of the corners in the front to head toward the back left, there was a huge object (about 3 times the size of the moon when it's closest to the earth) sitting on the tops of the palmetto trees located at the back of the prison property. i just stopped the truck and stared for a moment in disbelief. then i raced to the "hawk" post located at the back right corner of the prison. i jumped out of the truck and banged loudly on the door to be let in. i had tears streaming down my face and was hysterical. i was screaming for the officer in there to give me his binoculars. i got them and got back in the truck and sped back around to where i had seen the object but it was gone. i drove to the back of the prison and got out of the truck and just looked around up at the sky. after a little while i noticed two tiny lights in the sky that zigzagged up into the sky and disappeared. after about a half hour i received a call on the radio asking why i was not making my rounds around the perimeter of the prison by a lieutenant on the inside of the prison. i told him he needed to come outside. he did and i told him what i had seen and he went out back with me to have another look but i didn't see it again.
i knew when i first seen it that it could not have been from this world. the whole object glowed white but it also looked as if it had tiny white lights all over it.
please forgive my inability to draw well.
content.summary: Humungous round "moon-like" glowing orb with white lights covering whole thing hovering above treetops. two other small "dots" next to each other zigzag upward into the sky together.

content.detailedDescription: Me and my children were getting ready to watch the fireworks when we noticed an object changing colors and seemingly shape. i called my wife who was only a few blocks away and asked her to look.  we both took a video.  this lasted for about 15 20 min.  we couldn't imagine what it was. it stayed perfectly still and continued changing colors. thought it could possibly be a drone but didn't believe it to be.   we watched until it fell straight down out of sight. i thought the whole thing was something cool to witness.  about 5 10 min later i went to get my car when i noticed 2 red orbs by the train tracks.  the orbs were above to small trees.  i put the kids in the car and went looking for them.  as soon i i started driving i saw one above the building at south ave field.  i pulled my car around, got out and began recording again.  as i filmed the one another one came from the southeast, it was only 30 ft above the ground. it barely cleared a house and a tree.  it then came towards me and was only 3 4 ft off the ground and less than 50 ft away  meanwhile the first one ascended and made o u turn.  i could see through the bright light of the 2nd one. it was a bowling ball sized silver orb.  the light seemed to be like a curtain or drape.  it then went over the football field following the same direction of the first.  what struck me odd was that they didn't seem to have a purpose. like they were just looking around by this time i was extremely excited while my kids were scared. the one told me she thought they wanted me to leave them alone.

content.detailedDescription:
I was awakened by a driving wind storm against my bedroom window on approximately october 8, 1991.  as i listened to the the wind and the rain beat against the window wondering why such a storm was occurring both the wind and the rain  stopped abruptly.  suddenly  a beautiful blue light appeared.  i can't adequately describe the color except that it was soft, enormously beautiful & my perception was it was emanating from above my house. at that point i never saw anything except the blue light.  i got up and walked to the window in an attempt to see what was causing the light.  as i stood there looking,  about 500 feet away an orange orb suddenly  appeared.  it was small about 6 to 10  feet in diameter.  i thought an "telephone"  pole  electricity transformer had exploded.  the orb  was hovering (not moving).  in a few seconds it began to very slowly rise from  approximately 30 feet to 50 feet.  after a few seconds, the orb began to elongate and travel from where it was toward  my house.  it was approximately a  4 to  6 foot  wide "river" of smooth orange plasma about a 18 inches thick with rounded edges. it traveled from it's elevation down toward ground level and my house.   my perception and best description is it flowed more than being projected toward me.  it flowed at a measured pace i estimate to have been about 20 miles an hour  but not like a flash.  i was not fearful only curious and puzzled.  as i continued to watch, the leading edge of the plasma flow reached the edge of the blue light and both the orb and the light vanished in an instant.  there was no flash or explosion.  they just vanished as inexplicably as they appeared.    i was  shocked, dumbfounded and enormously astonished.  i went to wake  my wife who had a cold and was sleeping in a bedroom across the hall.  she was up and drowsy asking me what were "all the lights".  

i have been curious about  this and a couple of other very odd events that occurred over the next 30 days or so.  i've only told members of my family because i didn't want to be thought of as a kook of some sort.  although i believe there must be  a logical answer to this event i cannot explain what it was  i witnessed.  there are large electric transmission towers within a half mile.  although they are not located in the direction of the light or the orb my best guess this event had something to do with those towers and  the electricity they carry.

i'ver never had anything like this occur since 1991.  it's helpful to finally write it down.  this occurred  in a residential area east of seattle.  it would be very interesting to know  if there was  any other odd experiences recorded in this area in october of 1991.
content.summary: Steady blue light, moving orange orb, wind and rain.

content.detailedDescription:
I was smoking a cigarette in my backyard at night. there were no clouds and the stars were clearly visible. i noticed a strange noise on the other side of our fence. we have a lot of birds and squirrels, and i assume that’s all i heard. a moment or so after, one street over, a neighbor’s car alarm began ringing. 
now i normally stargaze at night when i go out for a cigarette. i like to spot shooting stars, nighttime planes, and the occasional satellite passing by. i just got my contact lens prescription updated, hence why i can clearly pic out a satellite passing through the stars at night. but back to the car alarm.
i hear the alarm go off. some neighborhood dogs start barking. i think nothing of it until i look up to the sky a few moments later. i look up to see a shooting star, but it wasn’t like the shooting stars i’ve seen in the past. it appeared much brighter than all the stars in the sky. it was traveling north/northwest. normally, the shooting stars i’ve seen always travel fast enough to leave a streak of light in their path.. this one seemed to travel much slower than others. it left no trail of light. it passed over and disappeared within 2-3 seconds. 
shooting stars i’ve seen previously leave me with an happy appreciation. this one left me wondering what exactly i just saw. i thought maybe it could have been a shooting star, a bird flying overhead highlighted by our streetlights, etc. 
after i finished my cigarette, i walked inside to find my family sturring over some strange knocking in the house. the family dog had been barking at the empty hallway, and they seemed mildly excited over the experience. i let them finish telling their story before i mentioned what i had seen outside so as not to influence their storyline. after we all exchanged our stories, we went back to enjoying the rest of our evening. 
i like to think ai have anpractical way at viewing the world around me. that being said; i do find myself interested in the unknown world/universe around us all. these could all have very well been independent, ordinary events happening in a small frame of time. however, the coincidence of them all happening so close together cannot leave me with some speculation. 
also, i failed to mention shortly after, i did notice two planes blinking inthe distance. we normally have a good number of planes in the airspace around my house at any given time, so i highly doubt there is any relation.
content.summary: Appeared to be shooting star, but moved too slowly. preceded by car alarm and dogs barking.
